First Lady Michelle Obama will be visiting Mexico City, Mexico from April 13-15, 2010. This will be her first solo official trip as First Lady. The visit aims to strengthen the ties between the United States and Mexico and promote mutual interests, respect, and responsibility between nations. Mrs. Obama will engage with the citizens of Mexico, especially young people, and continue discussions on education and economic advancement that she had with Mexican First Lady Margarita Zavala de Calderon.